a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x y :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 0.1"
and h1 : "y = 0.004"
shows  "x / y = 25"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 What is $0.1 \div 0.004$? The final Answer is 25
 ### Proof
 We have \[0.1\div 0.004 = \frac{0.1}{0.004} = \frac{0.1}{0.004}\cdot\frac{1000}{1000} = \frac{100}{4} = \boxed{25}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes x y :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 0.1"
and h1 : "y = 0.004"
shows  "x / y = 25"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
